commit_message:
Add venv_tag local fact

In order to make it easier to detect the currently deployed
venv for a service, and therefore allow smarter decisions
for things like upgrading, we implement the venv tag as a
local fact.

The file used to store facts will be the same for all
OpenStack services, with each service using its own section.

Example:

"ansible_local": {
    "openstack_ansible": {
        "sahara": {
            "venv_tag": "14.2.1"
        }
    }
}

Change-Id: I43a8895d111de16386a58acd30cc7a5e2c8259db
(cherry picked from commit afb4cfa352071a98cbabd4dce5860d290b71dc09)

Add support for endpoint group filtering

The following API calls are made available:

- GET /OS-EP-FILTER/projects/{project_id}/endpoint_groups
- GET /OS-EP-FILTER/endpoint_groups/{endpoint_group_id}/projects
- PUT /OS-EP-FILTER/endpoint_groups/{endpoint_group}/projects/{project_id}
- HEAD /OS-EP-FILTER/endpoint_groups/{endpoint_group}/projects/{project_id}
- DELETE /OS-EP-FILTER/endpoint_groups/{endpoint_group}/projects/{project_id}

